5 §2156.5. Building consultants
6 A. On and after January 1, 2026, any person who advertises, solicits,
7 undertakes, attempts, offers, or submits a price, bid, quote or estimate to construct,
8 supervise, advise, direct, oversee, or perform any construction, modification, repair,
9 or maintenance of any portion of a building shall hold the classification of building
10 consultant.
11 B. A building consultant shall meet all of the following requirements:
12 (1) Pass the building consultant examination which shall be administered
13 by the board.
14 (2) Meet all other certification requirements of a building consultant.
15 (3) Pay the necessary fees to the board for building consultants.
16 (4) Be subject to the board for oversight, compliance, and sanctions.
17 C. Building consultant is a subclassification of residential construction.
